<item>
            <title>[LU-2672] umask ignored on mkdir</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2672</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While testing on Sequoia, I noticed that Lustre appears to ignore my umask on directory creation.  I assume the umask is applied by libc and it is really the &quot;mode&quot; permissions in a lower level mkdir() that are not correctly honored.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On the client side (ppc64), I am running an experimental tag &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/chaos/lustre/commits/2.3.59-1chaos3morrone&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;2.3.59-1chaos3morrone&lt;/a&gt;.  On the server side (x86_64), we have tag &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/chaos/lustre/commits/2.3.58-6chaos&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;2.3.58-6chaos&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;No more info at this time.  Just noted in the process of other testing.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Sequoia, ppc64 client, x86_64 server</environment>
